Note: ============================================================================
Note: Main Parsing Functions
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Instruction-keyword dispatcher. Reads the instruction keyword (FROM,
RUN, CMD, etc.) and delegates to the corresponding parse_*_instruction
handler. The line/column from the keyword token are passed down so
each handler can attach the right source coordinates to its AST node.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Captures the keyword token's line and column. Reads the keyword
string. Long If-chain testing the keyword against each known
instruction name and routing to the appropriate parse handler.
Unknown keywords set a parser error and return 0.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_single_instruction" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:

    proc skip_newlines with parser_ptr

    Let is_end be proc is_at_end with parser_ptr
    If is_end is equal to 1:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let token_ptr be proc current_token with parser_ptr
    Let token_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with token_ptr, 0
    Let line_num be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with token_ptr, 16
    Let col_num be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with token_ptr, 24

    Note: Dispatch to appropriate instruction parser
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_FROM:
        proc advance with parser_ptr
        Let node_ptr be proc parse_from_instruction with parser_ptr, line_num, col_num
        Return node_ptr
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_RUN:
        proc advance with parser_ptr
        Set node_ptr to proc parse_run_instruction with parser_ptr, line_num, col_num
        Return node_ptr
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_CMD:
        proc advance with parser_ptr
        Set node_ptr to proc parse_cmd_instruction with parser_ptr, line_num, col_num
        Return node_ptr
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_LABEL:
        proc advance with parser_ptr
        Set node_ptr to proc parse_label_instruction with parser_ptr, line_num, col_num
        Return node_ptr
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_EXPOSE:
        proc advance with parser_ptr
        Set node_ptr to proc parse_expose_instruction with parser_ptr, line_num, col_num
        Return node_ptr
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_ENV:
        proc advance with parser_ptr
        Set node_ptr to proc parse_env_instruction with parser_ptr, line_num, col_num
        Return node_ptr
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_ADD:
        proc advance with parser_ptr
        Set node_ptr to proc parse_add_instruction with parser_ptr, line_num, col_num
        Return node_ptr
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_COPY:
        proc advance with parser_ptr
        Set node_ptr to proc parse_copy_instruction with parser_ptr, line_num, col_num
        Return node_ptr
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_ENTRYPOINT:
        proc advance with parser_ptr
        Set node_ptr to proc parse_entrypoint_instruction with parser_ptr, line_num, col_num
        Return node_ptr
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_VOLUME:
        proc advance with parser_ptr
        Set node_ptr to proc parse_volume_instruction with parser_ptr, line_num, col_num
        Return node_ptr
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_USER:
        proc advance with parser_ptr
        Set node_ptr to proc parse_user_instruction with parser_ptr, line_num, col_num
        Return node_ptr
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_WORKDIR:
        proc advance with parser_ptr
        Set node_ptr to proc parse_workdir_instruction with parser_ptr, line_num, col_num
        Return node_ptr
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_ARG:
        proc advance with parser_ptr
        Set node_ptr to proc parse_arg_instruction with parser_ptr, line_num, col_num
        Return node_ptr
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_ONBUILD:
        proc advance with parser_ptr
        Set node_ptr to proc parse_onbuild_instruction with parser_ptr, line_num, col_num
        Return node_ptr
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_STOPSIGNAL:
        proc advance with parser_ptr
        Set node_ptr to proc parse_stopsignal_instruction with parser_ptr, line_num, col_num
        Return node_ptr
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_HEALTHCHECK:
        proc advance with parser_ptr
        Set node_ptr to proc parse_healthcheck_instruction with parser_ptr, line_num, col_num
        Return node_ptr
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_SHELL:
        proc advance with parser_ptr
        Set node_ptr to proc parse_shell_instruction with parser_ptr, line_num, col_num
        Return node_ptr
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_MAINTAINER:
        proc advance with parser_ptr
        Set node_ptr to proc parse_maintainer_instruction with parser_ptr, line_num, col_num
        Return node_ptr
    End If

    proc set_error with parser_ptr, "Unknown instruction type"
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Top-level entry: parses the entire token stream into a
DockerfileAST root node containing all instructions in source order.
Used as the public-API hook for Dockerfile -> HIR translation.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocates a DockerfileAST root node with empty instructions list.
Loops while not at EOF: skips newlines, invokes
parse_single_instruction on the next instruction keyword, appends
the returned node to the instructions list. On parse error returns 0
to abandon partial output.
@End Implementation

Process called "parse_dockerfile" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:

    Let root_ptr be proc allocate from Memory with 32
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with root_ptr, 0, NODE_DOCKERFILE

    Let instructions_list be proc list_create from ListCore
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with root_ptr, 8, instructions_list
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with root_ptr, 16, 1  Note: line_number
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with root_ptr, 24, 1  Note: column_number

    Note: Parse all instructions
    Let continue be 1
    While continue is equal to 1:
        proc skip_newlines with parser_ptr

        Let is_end be proc is_at_end with parser_ptr
        If is_end is equal to 1:
            Set continue to 0
        Otherwise:
            Let instruction_ptr be proc parse_single_instruction with parser_ptr
            If instruction_ptr is equal to 0:
                Let has_error be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with parser_ptr, 32
                If has_error is equal to 1:
                    Return 0
                End If
                Set continue to 0
            Otherwise:
                proc list_append from ListCore with instructions_list, instruction_ptr

                Note: Consume trailing newline if present
                Let token_ptr be proc current_token with parser_ptr
                If token_ptr is not equal to 0:
                    Let token_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with token_ptr, 0
                    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_NEWLINE:
                        proc advance with parser_ptr
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End While

    Return root_ptr
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Helper Functions
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Joins a token list back into a single space-separated string. Used
by instruction parsers that need to capture the rest-of-line content
as one string (shell-form RUN/CMD/ENTRYPOINT, MAINTAINER, etc.).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Iterates the tokens list. For each token reads its lexeme via
get_token_lexeme and appends to a result string with a leading space
(suppressed on the first token).
@End Implementation

Process called "tokens_to_string" that takes tokens_ptr as Integer returns String:

    Let result be ""
    Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with tokens_ptr

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let token_ptr be proc list_get from ListCore with tokens_ptr, i
        Let lexeme be proc get_token_lexeme with token_ptr

        If i is greater than 0:
            Set result to proc string_concat from StringPrimitive with result, " "
        End If

        Set result to proc string_concat from StringPrimitive with result, lexeme
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return result
End Process
